snippet.textDisplay: Might be unpopular opinion, but I feel whoever directed this piece failed to do justice to any of the singers and their art forms. Overall the whole flow felt rushed and it appears that few things were just for "representation" purposes (e.g. RaviKishan's part was too short, at times the music and background singer's voices felt too overpowering and uncoordinated). These artists are so so talented and it just felt like they couldn't be themselves here, felt so unfair to me. I do understand this was fusion of various art forms, but at the end of the day, shouldn't it feel natural and not forced. I feel every single one deserves their own special video. Just my opinion, may be I have higher expectations from coke studio looking at the legacy that they have created.
